{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnixSocketAddressProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"SocketAddressProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO21SocketAddressProtocolP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketAddressProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UNIX domain sockets are generally visible in the filesystem."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"However, some systems support abstract socket names which are not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"visible in the filesystem and not affected by the filesystem"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"permissions, visibility, etc. Currently this is only supported","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"under Linux. If you attempt to use abstract sockets on other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"systems, function calls may return "},{"code":"G_IO_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"errors. You can use [func"},{"code":"Gio.UnixSocketAddress.abstract_names_supported","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to see if abstract names are supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.72, "},{"code":"GUnixSocketAddress","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is available on all platforms. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires underlying system support (such as Windows 10 with "},{"code":"AF_UNIX","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"run time.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineConten